  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nToday, it is not possible to define a collation when executing a query with the Hiberate ORM with Panache extension as we can in the MongoDB with Panache extension. \r\n\r\nWe want to implement filtering and sorting and apply a collation to be able to enable e.g. find case insensitive.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nDo the same as in #9081 but for Hibernate ORM with Panache (and also Hibernate reactive with Panache if collation is supported here). Some db supports collation, and it's usefull especially when an index is known to exist for a certain collation and we don't want massive slowdowns for using the connection default collation for which no index exists.",
